This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Clinton Moore Jr appeared by video.  Attorney Douglas J. Rebholz appeared by video for Clinton Moore Jr.  Prosecuting attorney Julie D Knyszek appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin. Deputy Court Clerk: SD. 
Pretrial Conference held.  Defense counsel requests additional pretrial conference date.  Case adjourned, Br. 41.
Pre-trial conference scheduled for November 18, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Justice Point Pretrial Services Report received and filed.
No contact order signed and filed.
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 3. Court ordered Defendant to maintain ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY. No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with CLF (8/24/1993). Court advised Defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Clinton Moore Jr appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Margo Elise Clark appeared by video for Clinton Moore Jr.  Prosecuting attorney Paul Christopher Dedinsky appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant is advised that due to the intake calendar of the week, this case has been re-assigned to Judge Skwierawski, Branch 41.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant pled not guilty.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.
Pre-trial conference scheduled for October 18, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Clinton Moore Jr not in court. Student Intern Abigail Doweiko in court under the supervision of Prosecuting attorney Thomas L. Potter by telephone for the State of Wisconsin. 
Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered an Arrest Warrant to be issued. Upon arrest, defendant is ordered remanded to a commissioner. Court ordered any bail on deposit to be forfeited. Court makes a finding that there is a possible victim identified and stays the forfeiture order with restitution to be determined at close of case.
Summons mailed.  Defendant ordered into room 221 Safety Building on 9/2/22 @ 2p
